	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't forget that by including an imbued gem in the armor, you are limiting who can use that armor.  The upside of imbued arms and armor? Imbued items grant stat increases based on the diety imbuing the gem.<br><br>Ferinstance:<br>Imbue Amber - Cazic Thule restricts any item using that gem to being used by followers of Cazic Thule ONLY.  Stat increases would be appropriate to followers of the God of Fear.<br><br>An item using a gem imbued by Rodcet Nife would grant different stats.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Thesipian Rogue of Bristlebane&lt;br&gt;<br>&lt;a href="<a href="http://i.am/amnesty/"&gt;Amnesty&lt;/a&gt;," target=_new>http://i.am/amnesty/"&gt;Amnesty&lt;/a&gt;,</a> Saryrn</td></tr>
