<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9678277531492></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9678277531492><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/skills.html?skill=8&mid=9678277531492>RE: food lasts longer ??</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79><span id= >Kral</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>12 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 1st 1:02 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>No, I think you are mistaken here.<br><br>Food/water does not go stale and rot away. It will keep forever if you do not consume it (put some in the bank and see). The rate at which you consume food is based on your race (big guys need to eat and drink more). Every n minutes, you will consume a drink/food. if you have none on you, you get the 'You are thirsty/hungry' message. Putting food in a container does not stop you having to eat...<br><br>As an aside, I also noticed that I tend to drink slightly more than I eat (Barbarian, with rations and water flasks). This usually equates to 1 more water than ration over a stack of 20. I keep meaning to try this out with other food to get some comparisons for length of time foods last, but have only really just started baking, so have not experimented with this too much.<br><br>Slightly out of topic - Baked foods also have the advantage of being lighter than rations, typically weighing 0.1 instead of 1. A small investment in baking can save you both carrying weight and money. You can buy ingrediants for typically the same price as rations, and produce food that weighs a lot less. With the right ingrediants, a success results in multiple food (mammoth sandwiches/steaks spring to mind, a success gives you 5! That's gotta be worth getting baking to 60-70, especially if you are in Halas).<br><br>Kral.<br>&nbsp;<br>Traveler of the crooked path, Xegony.</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
